President Trump held a meeting in the Roosevelt Room with Vice President Pence, Secretary Tom Price, and Administrator Seema Verma to discuss the role of women in healthcare and the hardships caused by Obamacare. The President thanked Administrator Verma for her work in helping to repeal and replace Obamacare. He also acknowledged the important contributions of women in the healthcare industry and highlighted the increasing number of women in medical schools and as physicians and surgeons. The President emphasized the negative impact of Obamacare on doctors and healthcare professionals, as well as patients, due to limited choices and rising costs. Administrator Verma expressed her support for the American Health Care Act as a solution to the problems caused by Obamacare, including fewer choices and burdensome regulations for providers. The meeting ended with the President expressing his gratitude to all the attendees.